1
00:01:03,720 --> 00:01:04,319
Leng Fang,

2
00:01:04,760 --> 00:01:05,360
Leng Fang,

3
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:06,320
Leng Fang,

4
00:01:06,320 --> 00:01:06,960
wake up.

5
00:01:07,160 --> 00:01:07,890
She's alive.

6
00:01:11,760 --> 00:01:12,360
Leng Fang.

7
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:14,700
Where is Shengnan?

8
00:01:16,680 --> 00:01:18,120
Zeng Xiaoyi was here.

9
00:01:19,240 --> 00:01:19,840
After him!

10
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,120
Stop running!

11
00:01:27,320 --> 00:01:28,080
Hurry, go!

12
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:30,120
Stop running!

13
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:31,240
Stop!

14
00:01:31,240 --> 00:01:31,920
Stop running!

15
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:32,560
Stop!

16
00:01:32,840 --> 00:01:33,600
Zeng Xiaoyi,

17
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,280
stop being so stubborn.

18
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:40,160
Yijun.

19
00:01:40,320 --> 00:01:41,450
I can't run anymore.

20
00:01:42,759 --> 00:01:43,560
Tongtong.

21
00:01:43,560 --> 00:01:44,320
Shengnan.

22
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:45,680
Shengnan.

23
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:47,000
Shengnan.

24
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,080
Her name isn't Shengnan.

25
00:01:48,080 --> 00:01:49,210
Her name is Gu Yijun.

26
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:50,340
She is my daughter.

27
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:52,039
None of you can take her away.

28
00:01:52,039 --> 00:01:52,840
Shengnan,

29
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:54,160
come home with me. Shengnan.

30
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:55,400
This is my child.

31
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:56,400
Shengnan.

32
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:57,200
Let go.

33
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,080
Let go! Let go!

34
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:01,480
Let go!

35
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,080
Shengnan.

36
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:05,080
Yijun.

37
00:02:05,320 --> 00:02:06,440
Mom.

38
00:02:09,039 --> 00:02:10,440
Mom.

39
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:13,920
Mom.

40
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:16,640
Mom.

41
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,280
Mom.

42
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,920
Even if I leave that family,

43
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,320
I will never abandon Yijun.

44
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:33,100
I ran with all my might.

45
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:35,060
I chased with all my might.

46
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,420
Shengnan is still waiting for me.

47
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,220
Now there's no one to comfort her.

48
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:43,200
She must be so scared.

49
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:49,530
Your dad asked me

50
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:51,200
to bring this over.

51
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,600
He said you haven't been home in days.

52
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,660
He's worried you're not eating well.

53
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,130
I've already eaten.

54
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:02,320
As for me,

55
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,840
I'm just dropping it off.

56
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,440
It's up to you if you eat it.

57
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:09,360
By the way,

58
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:11,200
the trial for Leng Fang's case is over.

59
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,320
The testimony and evidence you provided were very helpful.

60
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,000
She was sentenced to one month of non-custodial enforcement.

61
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:16,329
What about Zeng Xiaoyi?

62
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:17,959
As for the case files,

63
00:04:17,959 --> 00:04:20,240
you provided over a dozen large volumes.

64
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:22,490
I guess they're still reviewing them.

65
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:26,520
These buns are shrimp-filled.

66
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,960
Your dad made them especially for you.

67
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:29,080
He also asked me to tell you,

68
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:30,080
just throw them away if you won't eat them.

69
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:30,920
It's hot,

70
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,730
and they will spoil.

71
00:04:33,200 --> 00:04:33,960
Then take them away.

72
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:35,080
I'm really not eating them.

73
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:35,920
Then,

74
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:37,570
throw them away.

75
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:07,600
I forgot.

76
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:09,480
This

77
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:11,360
ginger

78
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:13,720
bun...

79
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:15,370
It's good with vinegar.

80
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,560
Why didn't you knock?

81
00:05:19,480 --> 00:05:21,280
Do inspectors have to knock too?

82
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:53,680
Uncle,

83
00:06:55,159 --> 00:06:56,490
I want to report a crime.

84
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,659
You want to report a crime?

85
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:01,480
Then tell me,

86
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,000
who bullied you?

87
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,320
Dad killed Mom.

88
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:06,880
He is a murderer.

89
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,160
He is a bad person.

90
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:14,800
Lanlan.

91
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:16,520
Listen to me.

92
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:19,680
Mom passed away because she was sick.

93
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,560
No.

94
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,560
I saw everything.

95
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:23,560
Look.

96
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:25,440
These two smell different.

97
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:27,040
I saw Dad

98
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,640
switch these two medicines.

99
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,120
Lanlan.

100
00:07:36,520 --> 00:07:38,000
Is it possible

101
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:41,640
that Mom was very sick

102
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:43,560
but wouldn't take her medicine,

103
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:45,680
so Dad switched the bottles

104
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,880
just to get her to take it

105
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,130
and get better soon?

106
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,640
But I saw Dad

107
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,440
press a pillow over Mom's face.

108
00:07:53,840 --> 00:07:56,120
Then Mom stopped moving.

109
00:07:57,680 --> 00:07:58,520
Child,

110
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,800
what you saw isn't the truth.

111
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:01,800
You have to remember.

112
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:04,360
Your dad loves your mom more than you do.

113
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:05,680
Everything he did

114
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:07,000
was for Mom's own good.

115
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,300
Do you understand?

116
00:08:08,400 --> 00:08:10,460
You keep saying it's for her own good.

117
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:12,480
But she still died.

118
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,520
If it was really for her own good,

119
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,640
then why did she die?

120
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:19,280
Why?

121
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:20,240
Lanlan.

122
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:21,680
Don't be sad.

123
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:27,200
You'll understand when you grow up.

124
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,560
Sometimes,

125
00:08:29,520 --> 00:08:30,980
the truth doesn't matter.

126
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,919
When I grow up,

127
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:35,720
I want to be a police officer like you.

128
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,080
I want to know the truth.

129
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:00,920
What's wrong?

130
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,420
Did someone bully you?

131
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,120
No.

132
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:07,450
The steamed buns were just too delicious.

133
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:15,200
It can't be delicious enough to make you cry.

134
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,660
Why are you reading a French book?

135
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:32,880
I was hoping you could translate it for me.

136
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:41,000
Forensic Science Research.

137
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:47,360
You mentioned that Lo-something-d before.

138
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:48,800
Locard's exchange principle.

139
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:49,360
Right.

140
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,640
I think it makes sense,

141
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,600
so I want to learn about it.

142
00:10:05,800 --> 00:10:06,840
Write neatly.

143
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:08,000
Got it.

144
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,040
I heard

145
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:15,000
that blood tests abroad

146
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,320
can now identify specific individuals.

147
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:19,520
We can only identify blood types.

148
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:21,100
The scope is too broad,

149
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:23,180
and it can't be used as sole evidence.

150
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:25,240
If technology advances in the future,

151
00:10:25,240 --> 00:10:27,040
we'll be able to use blood

152
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,530
to directly find that specific murderer.

153
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,160
That should

154
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,920
happen very soon.

155
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:50,280
Sir,

156
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:52,160
Wang Guilan from Lianxi House.

157
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,160
Six today.

158
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,880
The officer is asking you.

159
00:10:56,880 --> 00:10:58,720
Answer whatever he asks.

160
00:11:00,680 --> 00:11:01,240
Name?

161
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:02,920
Wang Wanru.

162
00:11:03,680 --> 00:11:04,320
Age?

163
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:05,400
19.

164
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,360
Reason.

165
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,730
Reason for being a prostitute?

166
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:11,960
Poverty.

167
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,280
Voluntary?

168
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:23,960
Come.

169
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,340
Concubine.

170
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,080
Name?

171
00:11:35,160 --> 00:11:35,960
What's wrong?

172
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:37,440
My stomach hurts.

173
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:38,940
I need to use the bathroom.

174
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:40,690
Why are you so much trouble?

175
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:43,480
There's one upstairs.

176
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,010
Hurry up.

177
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:47,520
Are you doing this voluntarily?

178
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:28,960
Name?

179
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:29,880
Li Pingyou.

180
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:33,400
Age.

181
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,480
Twenty.

182
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,120
Reason.

183
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:37,360
Debt.

184
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:49,440
What are you doing?

185
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:53,480
Can you help me?

186
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,520
Help me.

187
00:13:05,040 --> 00:13:06,040
Watch carefully.

188
00:13:17,520 --> 00:13:18,440
Help me, please.

189
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,240
Think of a way.

190
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:24,200
I didn't mean to default on the medicine bill.

191
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:24,840
My father...

192
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:26,320
The doctor says he's recovering.

193
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:28,240
Once he's well, he can pull the rickshaw again.

194
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:29,240
I have a younger brother.

195
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:31,400
He can work with me to pay off the debt.

196
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:32,920
I won't go back to Lianxi Tower.

197
00:13:32,920 --> 00:13:33,920
Inspector Zhang!

198
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:36,960
Inspector Zhang!

199
00:13:37,640 --> 00:13:38,970
What are you doing here?

200
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,360
Inspector Zhang.

201
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,560
A little bitch is hiding in your building.

202
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:44,090
You can't just ignore this.

203
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:44,800
All right.

204
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:45,640
Just talk.

205
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:46,840
Stop pulling at me.

206
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:48,040
This is the police station.

207
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:49,770
Why would we hide a prostitute?

208
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:52,240
What a thing to say.

209
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:53,640
What's wrong with prostitutes?

210
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:55,560
It's not like you don't visit often.

211
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:56,520
Besides,

212
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:58,360
didn't you benefit from it too?

213
00:13:58,360 --> 00:13:59,760
Alright, that's enough.

214
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,160
Later,

215
00:14:01,160 --> 00:14:02,680
leave her name here.

216
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:04,440
We'll send her back if we find her.

217
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:06,640
I won't take her if she's missing a limb.

218
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:08,440
I can't explain that away.

219
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:10,920
Thank you, Inspector Zhang.

220
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:26,840
That temper of yours.

221
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,860
Medical Examiner Qin is here too.

222
00:14:31,640 --> 00:14:33,440
We're exchanging ideas.

223
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:37,440
I asked Dr. Qin to fill me in

224
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:39,520
on the latest forensic research.

225
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,560
Work isn't important.

226
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:42,800
You two.

227
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:44,720
Don't just talk about

228
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:48,440
solving cases

229
00:14:48,440 --> 00:14:49,320
and work.

230
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:49,760
Right?

231
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:50,960
Look,

232
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,600
the weather is so nice.

233
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:53,400
You can go out,

234
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,560
go shopping,

235
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:55,760
or have some coffee.

236
00:14:58,120 --> 00:14:59,050
I'm drinking it.

237
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:02,400
You didn't invite Little Uncle.

238
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:03,280
Next time.

239
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:04,640
Next time.

240
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:17,290
You didn't go home to sleep again yesterday, did you?

241
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:22,640
Well...

242
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:26,200
I worked overtime yesterday, so I slept here.

243
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:33,380
The case is closed. Why are you still working overtime?

244
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:40,640
Just to save on the electricity bill.

245
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:43,000
Right. I really need to have a word with her next time.

246
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,260
Isn't this occupying public resources?

247
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,440
Thank you, Little Uncle.

248
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:49,300
I'll go out for coffee right away.

249
00:16:01,720 --> 00:16:02,720
What's your name?

250
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:03,920
Where do you live?

251
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:04,840
I'm Yingtao.

252
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,560
No. 156, Zhangyuan Lane.

253
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:33,960
Stop.

254
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:45,280
Uncle.

255
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:54,000
Who is she?

256
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:58,560
This is my friend from France.

257
00:17:05,160 --> 00:17:06,319
That's the spirit.

258
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:08,200
Make more friends.

259
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:10,000
Don't spend all your time at the police station.

260
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,329
It's good for you two to go out and have fun.

261
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:14,520
From France?

262
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:17,650
No wonder she looks so chic.

263
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,319
Take our Miss Lin

264
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:26,940
to have some good food.

265
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:30,720
We're off, Uncle.

266
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:31,840
Go ahead.

267
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:33,880
Goodbye, Uncle.
